1.2
log
@set the hash bucket size fixedly to 16384, to prevent it from
over-running to insane values if /etc/mail is on RAID level 1
(e.g. on herc, I got this before:
-rw-r-----  1 root  wheel  46006272 Oct 28 21:09 /etc/mail/aliases.db
and now I get
-rw-r-----  1 root  wheel  65536 Oct 28 21:11 /etc/mail/aliases.db
like I should)

Default size is 4096 or the filesystem block size. Using this
value of 16384 means "no change" for default MirOS but I have
no idea why it is not 8192...
@
